      is accurate and does not infringe the rights of others.</p>`,
  },
  {
    id: 'liability',
    title: '11. Disclaimers & Limitation of Liability',
    html: `
      <p>The Service is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, except those that cannot
      be excluded by law. To the fullest extent permitted by law, ${SITE.name} shall not be liable
      for any indirect, incidental or consequential loss arising from your use of the Service.</p>
      <p>Nothing in these Terms limits your statutory consumer rights or our liability for death,
      personal injury or fraud caused by our negligence.</p>`,
  },
  {
    id: 'governing-law',
    title: '12. Governing Law',
    html: `
      <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of France, and any dispute will be subject to the
      exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of Paris, without prejudice to any mandatory consumer
      protections available to you in your country of residence.</p>`,
  },
  {
    id: 'changes',
    title: '13. Changes to These Terms',
    html: `
      <p>We may update these Terms from time to time to reflect changes to our practices or the
      law. The current version is always posted on this page with its effective date. Continued
      use of the Service after changes take effect constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.</p>`,
  },
  {
    id: 'contact',
    title: '14. Contact Us',
    html: `
      <p>Questions about these Terms? We're glad to help.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}">${SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a></li>
        <li>Post: 12 Rue Saint-Honoré, 75001 Paris, France</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Or reach our client team through the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.</p>`,
  },
];

// ── Build a unified view model from whichever source we have ─────
let bodyHtml: string;
let toc: TocEntry[];
const usingShopify = Boolean(policy?.body?.trim());

if (usingShopify) {
  // Shopify's rendered policy HTML marks section titles with <strong>
  // (e.g. "OVERVIEW", "SECTION 1 - ONLINE STORE TERMS") rather than real
  // headings. Promote those to anchored, on-brand block headings so the
  // rail, scrollspy and visual hierarchy all work off the live content.
  // Any <h2> the merchant added by hand is also picked up.
  toc = [];
  const seen = new Set<string>();
  const addAnchor = (label: string): string => {
    let id = slugify(label);
    while (seen.has(id)) id += '-x';
    seen.add(id);
    toc.push({ id, label: prettyHeading(label) });
    return id;
  };

  bodyHtml = policy!.body
    // Section labels: <strong>OVERVIEW</strong> / <strong>SECTION n - …</strong>
    .replace(
      /<strong>\s*(OVERVIEW\b[^<]*|SECTION\s+\d+[^<]*?)\s*<\/strong>\s*(?:<br\s*\/?>\s*)?/gi,
      (_match, raw: string) => {
        const id = addAnchor(raw.trim());
        return `<strong id="${id}" class="tp-h scroll-mt-[110px]">${prettyHeading(raw.trim())}</strong>`;
      },
    )
    // Any explicit <h2> headings (hand-authored policies).
    .replace(/<h2([^>]*)>([\s\S]*?)<\/h2>/gi, (match, attrs: string, inner: string) => {
      if (/\bid=/.test(attrs)) return match;
      const label = inner.replace(/<[^>]+>/g, '').trim();
      if (!label) return match;
      const id = addAnchor(label);
      return `<h2${attrs} id="${id}" class="scroll-mt-[110px]">${inner}</h2>`;
    });
} else {
  toc = fallbackSections.map((s) => ({ id: s.id, label: s.title }));
  bodyHtml = fallbackSections
    .map(
      (s) =>
        `<section id="${s.id}" class="scroll-mt-[110px] [&:not(:first-child)]:mt-11">` +
        `<h2>${s.title}</h2>${s.html}</section>`,
    )
    .join('\n');
}

const title = policy?.title ?? 'Terms & Conditions';
const description =
  'The terms and conditions that govern your use of ' +
  `${SITE.name} and every order you place with us.`;
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  {/* ===================== HERO ===================== */}
  <section class="py-hero">
    <div class="container-mag" data-enter data-stagger>
      <span class="mag-label mb-[18px]">Legal · Issue N°02</span>
      <div class="flex flex-col items-start justify-between gap-8 lg:flex-row lg:items-end">
        <h1 class="h1 uppercase">Terms &amp; <em class="not-italic text-coral">Conditions.</em></h1>
        <p class="max-w-[440px] text-base leading-[1.65] text-text-secondary">
          The agreement between you and {SITE.name} — covering orders, payment, delivery, returns
          and your rights when you shop with us. Please read it carefully.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div
        class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-6 gap-y-2 text-[13px] text-text-muted"
      >
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="clock" size={15} class="text-coral" /> Last updated {LAST_UPDATED}
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="clock" size={15} class="text-coral" /> ~5 minute read
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ===================== BODY ===================== */}
  <section class="pb-section">
    <div class="container-mag">
      <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[240px_minmax(0,1fr)] lg:gap-12">
        {/* ── Table of contents: horizontal scroll on mobile, sticky on desktop ── */}
        <aside class="lg:sticky lg:top-[100px] lg:self-start">
          {
            toc.length > 0 && (
              <>
                <p class="mb-3 hidden text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-[1.6px] text-text-muted lg:block">
                  On this page
                </p>
                <nav
                  aria-label="Terms sections"
                  class="-mx-1 flex gap-2 overflow-x-auto px-1 pb-1 lg:mx-0 lg:flex-col lg:gap-1 lg:overflow-visible lg:px-0 lg:pb-0"
                >
                  {toc.map((t) => (
                    <a
                      href={`#${t.id}`}
                      data-toc-nav={t.id}
                      class="toc-link flex flex-none items-center rounded-sm px-4 py-2.5 text-[13.5px] font-semibold text-text-secondary transition-fluid hover:bg-surface-cool hover:text-coral lg:flex-auto"
                    >
                      <span class="whitespace-nowrap lg:whitespace-normal">{t.label}</span>
                    </a>
                  ))}
                </nav>
              </>
            )
          }

          {/* Support card — desktop only */}
          <div class="mt-6 hidden rounded-lg bg-dark p-5 text-white lg:block">
            <h3 class="font-heading text-[19px] font-bold leading-[1.1]">Need a hand?</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[13px] leading-[1.55] text-white/70">
              Questions about these terms? Our Paris team replies within 24 hours.
            </p>
            <a
              href="/contact"
              class="btn mt-4 inline-flex h-11 items-center gap-2 rounded-xs bg-coral px-5 text-white transition-fluid hover:bg-coral-hover"
            >
              Contact us <Icon name="arrowRight" size={15} />
            </a>
          </div>
        </aside>

        {/* ── Legal content ──────────────────────────────── */}
        <div class="min-w-0">
          {/* Intro notice */}
          <div
            class="mb-9 flex items-start gap-3.5 rounded-md bg-coral-soft px-5 py-4 text-[13.5px] leading-[1.6] text-text-secondary"
            data-reveal
          >
            <Icon name="shield" size={20} class="mt-0.5 flex-none text-coral" />
            <p>
              By using {SITE.name} or placing an order, you agree to these Terms. They sit
              alongside our <a href="/pages/privacy" class="font-semibold text-coral underline">Privacy
              Policy</a>. If anything is unclear, please <a href="/contact" class="font-semibold text-coral underline">get in touch</a> before you buy.
            </p>
          </div>

          <article class="rte max-w-none" data-terms-body set:html={bodyHtml} data-reveal />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ===================== CLOSING CTA ===================== */}
  <section class="pb-section">
    <div class="container-mag">
      <div
        class="flex flex-col items-center gap-5 rounded-xl bg-surface-cool px-6 py-12 text-center ring-1 ring-inset ring-border md:flex-row md:justify-between md:px-12 md:text-left"
        data-reveal
      >
        <div>
          <span class="mag-label mb-3">Still Reading</span>
          <h2 class="h3">Questions about <em class="not-italic text-coral">the fine print?</em></h2>
          <p class="mt-2 max-w-[520px] text-[14.5px] leading-[1.6] text-text-secondary">
            Our client team is happy to talk you through anything in these terms — from returns to
            delivery — usually within 24 hours.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-none flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
          <a
            href="/contact"
            class="btn inline-flex h-12 items-center gap-2.5 rounded-sm bg-coral px-6 text-white transition-fluid hover:bg-coral-hover"
          >
            Contact us <Icon name="arrowRight" size={16} />
          </a>
          <a
            href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}
            class="btn inline-flex h-12 items-center gap-2 rounded-sm border border-border bg-surface px-6 text-text-primary transition-fluid hover:border-dark hover:text-coral"
          >
            <Icon name="mail" size={16} /> Email us
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ============================================================
       Scrollspy — highlights the active section in the rail as you
       read. Idempotent + View-Transition safe. Anchor offset is
       handled by the scroll-mt utility on each heading/section.
       ============================================================ */}
  <script>
    function initTermsToc(): void {
      const body = document.querySelector<HTMLElement>('[data-terms-body]');
      if (!body || body.dataset.tocBound) return;
      body.dataset.tocBound = 'true';

      const navLinks = Array.from(
        document.querySelectorAll<HTMLAnchorElement>('[data-toc-nav]'),
      );
      // Anchors are either <section id> (fallback) or <h2 id> (Shopify).
      const targets = navLinks
        .map((l) => document.getElementById(l.getAttribute('data-toc-nav') ?? ''))
        .filter((el): el is HTMLElement => Boolean(el));
      if (!targets.length) return;

      const setActive = (id: string): void => {
        navLinks.forEach((l) =>
          l.classList.toggle('is-active', l.getAttribute('data-toc-nav') === id),
        );
      };

      if ('IntersectionObserver' in window) {
        const io = new IntersectionObserver(
          (entries) => {
            const visible = entries
              .filter((e) => e.isIntersecting)
              .sort((a, b) => a.boundingClientRect.top - b.boundingClientRect.top)[0];
            if (visible) setActive(visible.target.id);
          },
          { rootMargin: '-120px 0px -70% 0px', threshold: 0 },
        );
        targets.forEach((t) => io.observe(t));
      }
      setActive(targets[0].id);
    }

    initTermsToc();
    document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', initTermsToc);
  </script>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Active section in the rail (mirrors the FAQ rail). */
  .toc-link.is-active {
    background: var(--color-coral-soft);
    color: var(--color-coral);
  }
</style>

<style is:global>
  /* Section labels promoted from Shopify's <strong> markers into
     editorial block headings. Scoped under .rte so it never leaks.
     (set:html content carries no scope attribute, hence is:global.) */
  .rte strong.tp-h {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: 0.2px;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }
  .rte strong.tp-h:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
</style>
